meta_info <- data.frame(Sample_id = colnames(gut_2_group), Group = unlist(lapply(strsplit(colnames(gut_2_group),
    "_"), "[[", 1)))

dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = gut_2_group, colData = meta_info, design = ~Group)

#  dds 1
# 
dds <- dds[rowSums(counts(dds)) > 1, ]
# 
dds <- DESeq(dds)

normalized_counts <- counts(dds, normalized = T)
normalized_mean_counts = t(apply(normalized_counts, 1, function(a) {
    tapply(a, meta_info$Group, mean)
}))

enrich_go_kegg <- function(gene_id) {
    result <- list()

    ensembl_2_entrezid <- bitr(gene_id, fromType = "ENSEMBL", toType = c("ENTREZID", "SYMBOL"),
        OrgDb = org.Mm.eg.db)

    ego_ALL <- enrichGO(gene = ensembl_2_entrezid$ENTREZID, OrgDb = org.Mm.eg.db, keyType = "ENTREZID",
        ont = "ALL", pAdjustMethod = "BH", minGSSize = 1, pvalueCutoff = 0.05, qvalueCutoff = 0.05,
        readable = TRUE)

    result$ego_all <- as.data.frame(ego_ALL)
    # kegg_id<-bitr_kegg(ensembl_2_entrezid$ENTREZID,fromType = 'ncbi-geneid',toType =
    # 'kegg',organism = 'mmu')

    kegg <- enrichKEGG(gene = ensembl_2_entrezid$ENTREZID, organism = "mmu", keyType = "kegg", pAdjustMethod = "BH",
        pvalueCutoff = 1, qvalueCutoff = 1)

    result$kegg <- kegg@result

    result$kegg_ALL <- kegg

    result$ego_ALL <- ego_ALL

    return(result)
}

library(clusterProfiler)
library(org.Mm.eg.db)
library(AnnotationDbi)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(gridExtra)
library(stringr)

#  GO 
process_go_analysis <- function(enrich_object, org_db, ont = "BP", pAdjustMethod = "BH", qvalueCutoff = 0.05) {
  #  p  top 10 
  top10_enrich <- enrich_object %>%
    arrange(pvalue) %>%
    slice_head(n = 10)
  
  # IDENSEMBL
  genes <- unlist(strsplit(top10_enrich$geneID, "/"))
  ensembl_ids <- mapIds(org_db, keys = genes, column = "ENSEMBL", keytype = "SYMBOL", multiVals = "first")
  
  #  NA 
  ensembl_ids <- na.omit(ensembl_ids)
  
  #  clusterProfiler  GO 
  ego_result <- enrichGO(gene = ensembl_ids,
                         OrgDb = org_db,
                         keyType = "ENSEMBL",
                         ont = ont,
                         pAdjustMethod = pAdjustMethod,
                         qvalueCutoff = qvalueCutoff)
  
  #  10  GO  p 
  ego_result@result <- ego_result@result %>%
    arrange(pvalue) %>%
    slice_head(n = 10)
  
  return(ego_result)
}

ego_result_supernatant <- process_go_analysis(enrich_supernatant_ego, org.Mm.eg.db)
ego_result_medium <- process_go_analysis(enrich_Medium_ego, org.Mm.eg.db)

#  Description 
ego_result_supernatant@result$Description <- str_wrap(ego_result_supernatant@result$Description, width = 30)

KEGG @ supernatant + Medium

library(dplyr)

library(stringr)

#  KEGG  data.frame
process_kegg_analysis <- function(enrich_object, top_n = 10) {
  #  p  top_n 
  top_enrich <- enrich_object %>%
    arrange(pvalue) %>%
    slice_head(n = top_n)
  
  #  Description  "Mus musculus (house mouse)"
  top_enrich$Description <- unlist(lapply(strsplit(top_enrich$Description, " - "), function(x) {
    desc <- x[1]
    str_remove(desc, "Mus musculus \\(house mouse\\)")
  }))
  
  # 
  top_enrich$Description <- str_wrap(top_enrich$Description, width = 30)
  
  return(top_enrich)
}

# TPM load('gut_2_group_results.rda')
gene_length <- read.table("gut_2group_feature_counts.txt", header = TRUE, row.names = 1)[rownames(gut_2_group),
    "Length"]

# TPM 
counts2TPM <- function(count, efflength) {
    RPK <- count/(efflength/1000)  #reads (reads per kilobase) 
    PMSC_rpk <- sum(RPK)/1e+06  #RPK (per million scaling factor ) 
    RPK/PMSC_rpk
}

gut_2_group_tpm <- as.data.frame(apply(gut_2_group, 2, counts2TPM, efflength = gene_length))

# t
gut_2_group_tpm <- gut_2_group_tpm %>%
  rowwise() %>%
  filter(sum(!is.na(c_across(starts_with("Medium")))) >= 2 & sum(!is.na(c_across(starts_with("supernatant")))) >= 2) %>%
  ungroup()

#  P 
gut_2_group_tpm <- gut_2_group_tpm %>%
  rowwise() %>%
  mutate(P_value = t.test(c_across(starts_with("Medium")), c_across(starts_with("supernatant")))$p.value) %>%
  ungroup()
rownames(gut_2_group_tpm) <- gut_2_group_tpm$Ensembl_id

gut_2_group_tpm_T_test_filtered <- gut_2_group_tpm %>%
  filter(!is.na(P_value))   %>%    #  P_value_T_test  NaN 
  filter(P_value < 0.001) %>%   #  P_value_T_test  0.001 
  arrange(P_value)  #  P_value_T_test

    arrange(pvalue) %>%
    group_by(group) %>%
    slice_head(n = 20) %>%

library(reshape2)  #

#  gene_list  gut_2_group_tpm 
common_genes <- intersect(gene_list$Ensembl_id, gut_2_group_tpm$Ensembl_id)

if (length(common_genes) == 0) {
  stop("")
} else {
  #  gene_list gut_2_group_tpm 
  gene_list <- gene_list[gene_list$Ensembl_id %in% common_genes, ]
}

# 
plot_gene_expression <- function(gene_id, gene_name, data) {
  selected_columns <- grep("Medium|supernatant", colnames(data))  #  "Medium"  "supernatant" 
  gene_data <- data[gene_id, selected_columns, drop = FALSE]  # 
  
  # 
  gene_data <- gene_data[, colSums(is.na(gene_data)) == 0]
  
  if (ncol(gene_data) == 0) {
    return(NULL)  # NULL
  }
  
  gene_data <- as.data.frame(t(gene_data))  # 
  gene_data$Sample <- rownames(gene_data)  # 
  colnames(gene_data)[1] <- "TPM"  #  "TPM"
  
  # 
  gene_data_melted <- melt(gene_data, id.vars = "Sample")  # 
  gene_data_melted$Group <- ifelse(grepl("Medium", gene_data_melted$Sample), "Medium", "supernatant")  # 
  
  #  Group 
  gene_data_melted$Group <- factor(gene_data_melted$Group, levels = c("Medium", "supernatant"))
  
  #  t  p 
  t_test_result <- t.test(value ~ Group, data = gene_data_melted)
  p_value <- t_test_result$p.value
  
  #  p  p 
  if (!is.na(p_value) && p_value < 0.05) {
    print(paste(gene_name, "Tp ", p_value))  # p
    
    # 
    gene_plot <- ggplot(gene_data_melted, aes(x = Group, y = value)) +  #  ggplot 
      geom_boxplot(aes(fill = Group), alpha = 0.7) +  # 
      scale_fill_manual(values = c('Medium' = "#0072C1", 'supernatant' = "#9F1326")) +  # 
      theme_classic() +  # 
      xlab("") + ylab("TPM") + ggtitle(gene_name) +  # 
      theme(
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 14, face = "bold", vjust = 1),  # 
        axis.text = element_text(color = 'black', size = 14, face = "bold"),  # 
        axis.title.y = element_text(color = 'black', size = 14, face = "bold"),  # y
        legend.text = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),  # 
        legend.background = element_rect(fill = "transparent"),  # 
        legend.title = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),  # 
        legend.position = "right",  # 
        axis.text.x = element_blank(),  # x
        axis.ticks.x = element_blank(),  # x
        panel.background = element_rect(fill = "transparent"),  # 
        plot.background = element_rect(fill = "transparent", color = NA)  # 
      ) +
      geom_signif(
        comparisons = list(c("Medium", "supernatant")),  # 
        map_signif_level = TRUE,                         # 
        textsize = 4,                                    # 
        test = "t.test",                                 #  t 
        tip_length = 0,                                  # 
        y_position = max(gene_data_melted$value, na.rm = TRUE) * 1  # 
      ) +
      annotate("text", x = 1.5, y = max(gene_data_melted$value, na.rm = TRUE) * 1.3, 
               label = paste("p =", round(p_value, 4)), size = 5, color = "black", fontface = "bold")  # p
    
    return(gene_plot)
  } else {
    print(paste(gene_name, "TP", p_value, ""))  # p
    return(NULL)  #  p NULL
  }
}

# 
plot_list <- lapply(1:nrow(gene_list), function(i) {
  gene_id <- gene_list$Ensembl_id[i]
  gene_name <- gene_list$Symbol[i]
  plot_gene_expression(gene_id, gene_name, gut_2_group_tpm)
})
